			<div class="content" id="post-content-4860158">
									

<blockquote>
<p>They are not entities, IS is this universe and everything that exists in it, IS NOT are the impossible concepts that should not be, usually aren't but occasionally are even though they shouldn't, and some anomalies kind of fall in between.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yeah, after rereading SCP-4840, I think your interpretation is pretty good. After looking over it now, its become clear to me that IS and IS NOT are at least related to the 'Question Entities' from SCP-5935, as they act almost identically - in the sense that they can act and seem alive (like the entity made of names does in 5935, and as both the serpent and <a href="/scp-3000">his dark brother</a> do) From that, I'd hazard a guess that IS and IS NOT were two questions: &quot;What is?&quot; and &quot;What isn't?&quot; respectively, and the asking of these questions created the universe. Then the books in the old library would be the answers to these questions, but that's just my headcanon.</p>
<p>On Eve, She could be out their somewhere, but that's for other writers to figure out. In terms of the locations for early humans:</p>
<ul>
<li>Lilith - Foundation Containment as <a href="/scp-336">SCP-336</a></li>
<li>Adam El Asem - in <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2932">Titania's Prison</a><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-67444-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-67444-1')">1</a></sup></li>
<li>Cain - Foundation containment as <a href="/scp-073">SCP-073</a></li>
<li>Able - Foundation containment as <a href="/scp-076">SCP-076</a></li>
<li>Seth - On Audapopadopolis as <a href="/scp-4840">SCP-4840-B</a></li>
</ul>
<p>In terms of their descendants, I have no Idea.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
